<?xml version="1.0"?>
<Ontology xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#"
     xml:base="https://example.org/roadsigns"
     xmlns:rdf="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#"
     xmlns:xml="http://www.w3.org/XML/1998/namespace"
     xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#"
     xmlns:rdfs="http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#"
     ontologyIRI="https://example.org/roadsigns"
     versionIRI="https://example.org/roadsigns/5.0">
    <Prefix name="" IRI="https://example.org/roadsigns#"/>
    <Prefix name="owl" IRI="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#"/>
    <Prefix name="rdf" IRI="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#"/>
    <Prefix name="xml" IRI="http://www.w3.org/XML/1998/namespace"/>
    <Prefix name="xsd" IRI="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#"/>
    <Prefix name="rdfs" IRI="http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#"/>
    <Prefix name="roadsigns" IRI="https://example.org/roadsigns#"/>
    <Annotation>
        <AnnotationProperty abbreviatedIRI="rdfs:comment"/>
        <Literal xml:lang="en">Session 5 Focus:
(A) Reasoning: Verification of ontology consistency and inferred axioms using Semantic Reasoners such as HermiT or Pellet.
(B) Competency Questions (outside the Ontology): Formalization of domain-specific questions via DL queries, SPARQL, and Owlready2 Python scripts. Key questions include:
    - Primary kinds of road signs in the Vienna Convention.
    - Association of shapes (e.g., Circle, Triangle) with functional categories.
    - Standardized visual properties like background and border colors for specific models (e.g., B2a STOP sign).
    - Dataset-specific queries regarding image repository contents and sign frequency.

Session 6 Note:
While Session 5 focuses on reasoning and validation, Session 6 transitions toward project submission, methodology defense, and the integration of these formalizations into a final knowledge engineering pipeline.

Base IRI: https://example.org/roadsigns#
All class names, object-property names, and data-property names are preserved
verbatim from Sessions 1-4.
Vienna Convention on Road Signs and Signals (Part I, Annex 1).
Aligned with Mapillary Traffic Sign Dataset (MTSD) class labels.</Literal>
    </Annotation>
    <Annotation>
        <AnnotationProperty abbreviatedIRI="rdfs:label"/>
        <Literal xml:lang="en">Road Signs Ontology — Session 5: Reasoning and Competency Questions.</Literal>
    </Annotation>
