        <IRI>#RoundaboutSign</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="en">Defined by the Vienna Convention as Sign D, 3. Notifies drivers they must follow the direction indicated by the arrows in a circular movement. 

Note: In Right-Hand Traffic (RHT) countries, circulation is anti-clockwise. Per Article 8, in Left-Hand Traffic (LHT) countries like Ireland, the symbol is mirrored to indicate clockwise circulation.</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty abbreviatedIRI="rdfs:label"/>
        <IRI>#RoundaboutSign</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="en">Roundabout Sign</Literal>
